# Copy to `.env` in this folder (Vite injects `VITE_*` into the client bundle).
# VITE_RPC_URL=https://api.mainnet-beta.solana.com
# VITE_TOKEN_MINT=EPjFWdd5AufqSSqeM2qN1xzybapC8G4wEGGkZwyTDt1v
# VITE_SOL_BOT_MAX_INPUT_RAW=5000000
# VITE_MODE=paper
# VITE_SOL_BOT_KILL_SWITCH=0
# Optional client override for Jupiter base (public deploys without Vite proxy):
# VITE_JUPITER_API_BASE=https://quote-api.jup.ag/v6
#
# --- Vite dev server only (not VITE_*): Jupiter upstream for `/jupiter-api` proxy ---
# Default: https://quote-api.jup.ag
# If you terminate Jupiter on your own host (nginx, etc.):
# JUPITER_API_PROXY_TARGET=https://your-internal-host
#
# --- When Vite logs `getaddrinfo ENOTFOUND quote-api.jup.ag` ---
# Your VM cannot resolve DNS for Jupiter. Fix system DNS, e.g. Ubuntu:
#   sudo resolvectl dns "$(ip -4 route show default | awk '{print $5}' | head -1)" 8.8.8.8 1.1.1.1
#   sudo resolvectl flush-caches
# Test: getent hosts quote-api.jup.ag
#
# --- When curl shows `CONNECT tunnel failed` or proxy breaks Node ---
# A broken HTTP(S)_PROXY is forcing CONNECT. From repo root use:
#   npm run chart:dev:direct-net
# or unset HTTPS_PROXY http_proxy HTTP_PROXY all_proxy for the shell that starts Vite.
